Including file: vWin32fh.pkg    (C:\Projects\DF18\DbUpdateFramework\AppSrc\vWin32fh.pkg)
79633>>>// This code is part of VDF GUIdance
79633>>>// Visit us @ http://www.vdf-guidance.com
79633>>>// e-Mail us @ info@vdf-guidance.com
79633>>>// VDF GUIdance is a mutual project of
79633>>>// Frank Vandervelpen - Vandervelpen Systems and
79633>>>// Wil van Antwerpen  - Antwise Solutions
79633>>>// All software source code should be used <<AS IS>> without any warranty.
79633>>>//
79633>>>//
79633>>>// *** Windows 32bit file handling wrapper class ***
79633>>>//
79633>>>
79633>>>// 05-09-2000 **WvA: Changed namingconvention of all classes and methods to new standard
79633>>>//                   This may be painfull for some of you, but it was really needed as it was
79633>>>//                   getting messy. The "vs" -prefix we used before was confusing and could
79633>>>//                   unintentionally have been interpreted as "Vdf-GUIdance String".
79633>>>//
79633>>>// The used naming-convention is:
79633>>>//     - a prefix of "vWin32_" for every external function declaration
79633>>>//     - a prefix of the letter "v" for the full API name for the vdf-wrapper function.
79633>>>//
79633>>>// By using this we are guarding ourselves for conflicts with variable declarations
79633>>>// of DataAccess in the future.
79633>>>// Or at least almost as the letter "v" is now also synonym for variant (duh~!)
79633>>>//
79633>>>// mm-dd-yyyy Author Description
79633>>>//
79633>>>//                   vSHGetFolderPath added to retrieve the new shell folders
79633>>>//                   vGetWindowsDirectory
79633>>>//
79633>>>//                   vGetTempFileName
79633>>>//                   vGetTempPath
79633>>>// 11-17-2001 **WvA: Removed User Interface Error popups such as Error handling.
79633>>>//                   This is an absolute need for WebApp. We expect you to handle the
79633>>>//                   error in your application anyways. Changed this for:
79633>>>//                   vDeleteFile, vCopyFile, vMoveFile and vRenameFile
79633>>>// 03-02-2002 **WvA: vRemoveDirectory added
79633>>>// 03-11-2002 **WvA: The parameter lpdword in the external function declaration for
79633>>>//                   vWin32_SHBrowsForFolder can cause compiler errors.
79633>>>//                   It is renamed too avoid this.
79633>>>// 11-11-2002 **WvA: Codecleanup, vcSelectFile_Dialog is now cvSelectFile_Dialog, its
79633>>>//                   function vSelectedFileName is now just SelectedFileName
79633>>>//                   Removed the local keyword in the variable declarations
79633>>>// 10-17-2003 **WvA: Cleaned up function vSelect_File and added code to destroy the dynamically
79633>>>//                   created file-open dialog
79633>>>// 02-12-2004 **WvA: Allan Ankerstjeme pointed me into a bug for the vCreateTempFileInPath
79633>>>//                   in that it didn't exactly return the correct filename of the file created.
79633>>>//                   This has now been taken care of.
79633>>>// 02-19-2004 **WvA: Removed all API declarations from the package itself to improve readability
79633>>>//                   These declarations are now included from the vWin32fh header file.
79633>>>// 02-19-2004 **WvA: Changed the default way in which the standard file handling works
79633>>>//                   Before today one could always undo the operation, as of now you cannot as
79633>>>//                   the default was a silly one using unnecessary resources (mainly diskspace)
79633>>>//                   Since i don't really expect someone to use that feature it has been removed.
79633>>>//                   One can however restore to the old way of handling by simply calling the
79633>>>//                   vWin32fhCompatibilityMode procedure ONE time before accessing any of the
79633>>>//                   filehandling operations
79633>>>// 02-19-2004 **WvA: The functions ParseFolderName, ParseFileName and ParseFileExtenstion added
79633>>>//                   as well as the StringFromRightOfChar function.
79633>>>// 02-19-2004 **WvA: sfoFormatDisk function added which can use to format a floppydisk
79633>>>//                   DISABLED now as testing shows that it does not work as advertised...
79633>>>// 02-20-2004 **WvA: The function vDDE_Error_Handler didn't pass the errornumber on to the DDE_Error_To_String function
79633>>>//                   Moved the hardcoded strings from vDDE_Error_Handler to define declarations for easier translation later on.
79633>>>// 09-10-2004 **WvA: Added the ToAnsi function to the fileoperations method so that
79633>>>//                   extended characters are treated ok too.
79633>>>//                   Reported by Flemming from
79633>>>// 12-17-2004 **WvA: Changed vFilePathExists to be global, reported by Peter van Mil
79633>>>// 12-28-2004 **WvA: WebApp compatibility added by introducing compiler directives
79633>>>// 03-10-2006 **WvA: Added more CSIDL types to our header file for use with the vSHGetFolderPath function
79633>>>// 01-02-2007 **WvA: Set NoChangeDir_State on vSelect_File and vSelectSaveFile to True but changed it back due to side effects.
79633>>>//                   Added vSelectSavefile function to create a file save dialog
79633>>>//                   Fixed ParseFolderName which was horribly broken (thanks for the reports)
79633>>>//                   Added vParentPath function to retrieve the parent "node" of a path
79633>>>// 01-04-2008 **WvA: Fixed vCreateTempFileInPath as the function wasn't working
79633>>>// 10-04-2009 **WvA: Added vshCreateDirectoryEx from Micheal Mullan, moved filedialogs to cvFileDialogs.pkg
79633>>>// 01-11-2010 **WvA: Added vWin32_APIFilesize as supplied by Renato Villa, to get the filesize of the specified file. See http://support.dataaccess.com/forums/showthread.php?t=41982
79633>>>// 10-02-2011 **WvA: Added vCSIDL_SYSTEMX86, courtesy of Ola Eldoy for pointing this out and providing the define statement.
79633>>>// 20-12-2012 **WvA: Default behavior on copy/move is now to autocreate subfolders, tip by Frank Cheng
79633>>>// 29-09-2014 **WvA: Added function vFolderFileCount to count the number of files in a folder, add vCSIDL_PROGRAM_FILESx86
79633>>>// 04-10-2014 **WvA: Added extra checks on vFilePathExists and vFolderExists courtesy of Nils Svedmyr
