79699>>>>>
79699>>>>>
79699>>>>>// The ShellExecute function opens or prints a specified file. The file can be an
79699>>>>>// executable file or a document file.
79699>>>>>//
79699>>>>>// Operation can be one of the following:
79699>>>>>//    "OPEN"  The function opens the file specified by lpFile.
79699>>>>>//            The file can be an executable file or a document file.
79699>>>>>//            The file can be a folder to open.
79699>>>>>//    "PRINT" The function prints the file specified by lpFile.
79699>>>>>//            The file should be a document file. If the file is an executable file,
79699>>>>>//            the function opens the file, as if "open" had been specified.
79699>>>>>//  "EXPLORE" The function explores the folder specified by lpFile.
79699>>>>>//
79699>>>>>// Return Values:
79699>>>>>//
79699>>>>>// If the function succeeds, the return value is the instance handle of the application that
79699>>>>>// was run, or the handle of a dynamic data exchange (DDE) server application.
79699>>>>>// If the function fails, the return value is an error value that is less than or equal to 32.
79699>>>>>//
79699>>>>>// The following table lists these error values:
79699>>>>>// Public Const ERROR_FILE_NOT_FOUND = 2&
79699>>>>>// Public Const ERROR_PATH_NOT_FOUND = 3&
79699>>>>>// Public Const ERROR_BAD_FORMAT = 11&
79699>>>>>// Public Const SE_ERR_ACCESSDENIED = 5
79699>>>>>// Public Const SE_ERR_ASSOCINCOMPLETE = 27
79699>>>>>// Public Const SE_ERR_DDEBUSY = 30
79699>>>>>// Public Const SE_ERR_DDEFAIL = 29
79699>>>>>// Public Const SE_ERR_DDETIMEOUT = 28
79699>>>>>// Public Const SE_ERR_DLLNOTFOUND = 32
79699>>>>>// Public Const SE_ERR_FNF = 2
79699>>>>>// Public Const SE_ERR_NOASSOC = 31
79699>>>>>// Public Const SE_ERR_OOM = 8
79699>>>>>// Public Const SE_ERR_PNF = 3
79699>>>>>// Public Const SE_ERR_SHARE = 26
79699>>>>>
79699>>>>>
79699>>>>>
79699>>>>>// Code to open the program that is associated with the selected file.
79699>>>>>//
79699>>>>>// External function call used in Procedure DoStartDocument
79699>>>>>External_function vWin32_ShellExecute "ShellExecuteA" shell32.dll ;  Handle hWnd ;  Pointer lpOperation ;  Pointer lpFile ;  Pointer lpParameters ;  Pointer lpDirectory ;  Dword iShowCmd Returns Handle
