79714>>>>>
79714>>>>>// SHCreateDirectoryEx
79714>>>>>
79714>>>>>//    Note  This function is available through Microsoft Windows XP Service Pack 2 (SP2) and Windows Server 2003.
79714>>>>>//    It might be altered or unavailable in subsequent versions of Windows.
79714>>>>>//
79714>>>>>//    This function creates a file system folder whose fully qualified path is given by pszPath. If one or more
79714>>>>>//    of the intermediate folders do not exist, they are created as well. SHCreateDirectoryEx also verifies that
79714>>>>>//    the files are visible. If they are not visible, expect one of the following:
79714>>>>>//
79714>>>>>//        * If hwnd is set to a valid window handle, a message box is displayed warning the user that he or she
79714>>>>>//        might not be able to access the files. If the user chooses not to proceed, the function returns
79714>>>>>//        ERROR_CANCELLED.
79714>>>>>//        * If hwnd is set to NULL, no user interface is displayed and the function returns ERROR_CANCELLED.
79714>>>>>
79714>>>>>//        Returns ERROR_SUCCESS if successful. If the operation fails, other error codes can be returned,
79714>>>>>//        including those listed here. For values not specifically listed, see System Error Codes.
79714>>>>>//      161  ERROR_BAD_PATHNAME                The pszPath parameter was set to a relative path.
79714>>>>>//      206  ERROR_FILENAME_EXCED_RANGE     The path pointed to by pszPath is too long.
79714>>>>>//      3    ERROR_PATH_NOT_FOUND            The system cannot find the path pointed to by pszPath. The path may contain an invalid entry.
79714>>>>>//      80   ERROR_FILE_EXISTS                The directory exists.
79714>>>>>//      183  ERROR_ALREADY_EXISTS            The directory exists.
79714>>>>>//      1223 ERROR_CANCELLED                The user canceled the operation.
79714>>>>>
79714>>>>>//        int SHCreateDirectoryEx(
79714>>>>>//            HWND hwnd,
79714>>>>>//            LPCTSTR pszPath,
79714>>>>>//            const SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES *psa
79714>>>>>//        );
79714>>>>>
79714>>>>>External_function vWin32_SHCreateDirectoryEx "SHCreateDirectoryExA" shell32.dll Handle hWnd;                  pointer pszPath  Pointer lpSecurity_Attributes Returns Integer
