80850>>>//****************************************************************************
80850>>>// $Module type: Class
80850>>>// $Module name: cSQLConnectionHandler.pkg
80850>>>// $Author     : Nils G. Svedmyr, RDC Tools International, <mailto:support@rdctools.com>
80850>>>// Web-site    : http://www.rdctools.com
80850>>>// Created     : 2015-08-11 @ 16:02 (Military date format: YY-MM-DD)
80850>>>//
80850>>>// Description : A handler class for using CLI connection ID's to login to a database server.
80850>>>//
80850>>>// $Rev History:
80850>>>//    2015-08-11  Module header created
80850>>>//    2016-09-26  Changed name of the objecthandle from ghoCreateConnectionID to ghoSQLConnectionHandler.
80850>>>//                Added a new structure for passing connection data back & forth.
80850>>>//                Added better error handling.
80850>>>//                Added a decompose message for the connection string.
80850>>>//    2017-01-09  Added support for Mertech drivers
80850>>>//                Big overhaul to comply better with "Managed Connections" (DF 19)
80850>>>//                These changes make the class compatible with DFConnId.ini (can read/write DAW connection ini-files)
80850>>>//    2017-02-12  Reworked the whole connection property interface.
80850>>>//                Now there is one struct property that is the at cencter of a connection.
80850>>>//****************************************************************************
80850>>>Use cli.pkg
80850>>>Use MSSqldrv.pkg         
Including file: MSSqldrv.pkg    (C:\Program Files (x86)\DataFlex 19.0\Pkg\MSSqldrv.pkg)
80850>>>>>//*****************************************************************************
80850>>>>>//*** MSSQLDRV.PKG                                                          ***
80850>>>>>//***                                                                       ***
80850>>>>>//*** Author: Ben Weijers                                                   ***
80850>>>>>//***         Data Access Nederland                                         ***
80850>>>>>//***         29 June 1998                                                  ***
80850>>>>>//***                                                                       ***
80850>>>>>//***                                                                       ***
80850>>>>>//*** Purpose:                                                              ***
80850>>>>>//***   Package that declares MS SQL driver constants and functions.        ***
80850>>>>>//****                                                                      ***
80850>>>>>//***   This package can be used by developers who want to add Data Access  ***
80850>>>>>//***   MS SQL Client specific code to a DataFlex application.              ***
80850>>>>>//***   Updated:  June 4th 2012 (Current CK build: 5.1.0.96)                ***
80850>>>>>//***             Changed EnumerateServers function to use the highest      ***
80850>>>>>//***             available SQL Server client driver.                       ***
80850>>>>>//***             Moved SQL Server client constants from cli.pkg to         ***
80850>>>>>//***             mssqldrv.pkg                                              ***
80850>>>>>//***   Updated:  November 6th 2013 (Current CK build: 6.0.0.19)            ***
80850>>>>>//***             Added constants for SQL Server specific native types      ***
80850>>>>>//***             ( var...(max) types, money types, datetime types)         ***
80850>>>>>//*****************************************************************************
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>Use Cli.pkg
80850>>>>>Use SQL.pkg
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>//*** Driver Indentification
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>//*** Error number constants
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>//*** Possible DF_DRIVER_SQLSERVER_CLIENT_VERSION values
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>// SQL Server spcific types. 
80850>>>>>Define SQL_SS_TIMESTAMPOFFSET   for   (-155) //SQL server datetimeoffset type */
80850>>>>>Define SQL_SS_TIME2             for   (-154) //SQL server time type */
80850>>>>>Define SQL_SS_XML               for   (-152) //SQL server xml type */
80850>>>>>Define SQL_SS_VARIANT           for   (-150) //SQL server variant type */
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>// SQL Server spcific types. 
80850>>>>>Define SQL_TYPE_TIMESTAMP2      for   (-200) //SQL server datetime2 type */
80850>>>>>Define SQL_VARCHARMAX           for   (-201) //SQL server varchar(max) type */
80850>>>>>Define SQL_WVARCHARMAX          for   (-202) //SQL server wvarchar(max) type */
80850>>>>>Define SQL_VARBINARYMAX         for   (-203) //SQL server varbinary(max) type */
80850>>>>>Define SQL_TYPE_MONEY           for   (-204) //SQL server money type */
80850>>>>>Define SQL_TYPE_SMALLMONEY      for   (-205) //SQL server smallmoney type */
80850>>>>>Define SQL_TYPE_SMALLDATETIME   for   (-206) //SQL server smalldatetype type */
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>//*****************************************************************************
80850>>>>>//*** MSSQL_SetConstraint <FileNum> <ConstraintText>                        ***
80850>>>>>//***                                                                       ***
80850>>>>>//***   Setup a constraint for a file.                                      ***
80850>>>>>//*****************************************************************************
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>
80850>>>>>Class cMSSQLHandler Is A cCLIHandler
80851>>>>>
80851>>>>>    Procedure Construct_Object
80853>>>>>        Forward Send Construct_Object
80855>>>>>
80855>>>>>        Set psDriverID To MSSQLDRV_ID
80856>>>>>    End_Procedure // Construct_Object
80857>>>>>
80857>>>>>
80857>>>>>
80857>>>>>    //***
80857>>>>>    //*** Function: ExtractList
80857>>>>>    //*** Purpose : Extract the list from the out connect string.
80857>>>>>    //***
80857>>>>>
80857>>>>>    Function ExtractList String sOutConnStr Integer hoStore Returns Integer
80859>>>>>        Local String  sItem
80859>>>>>        Local Integer iStart
80859>>>>>        Local Integer iEnd
80859>>>>>
80859>>>>>        If (hoStore = 0) ;            Move Current_object To hoStore
80862>>>>>
80862>>>>>        Send Delete_Data To hoStore
80863>>>>>        Move (Pos("{", sOutConnStr)) To iStart
80864>>>>>        While (iStart > 0)
80868>>>>>            Move (Right(sOutConnStr, Length(sOutConnStr) - iStart)) To sOutConnStr
80869>>>>>            If (Left(sOutConnStr, 1) = "}") ;                Move 0 To iStart
80872>>>>>            Else Begin
80873>>>>>                Move (Pos(",", sOutConnStr)) To iStart
80874>>>>>                Move (Pos("}", sOutConnStr)) To iEnd
80875>>>>>                If ((iStart = 0) Or (iEnd < iStart)) ;                    Move iEnd To iStart
80878>>>>>
80878>>>>>                If (iStart > 0) ;                    Set Value Of hoStore Item (Item_Count(Current_Object)) To (Left(sOutConnStr, iStart - 1))
80881>>>>>
80881>>>>>                If (iStart = iEnd) ;                    Move 0 To iStart
80884>>>>>            End
80884>>>>>>
80884>>>>>        Loop
80885>>>>>>
80885>>>>>
80885>>>>>        Function_Return (Item_Count(hoStore))
80886>>>>>    End_Procedure // ExtractList
80887>>>>>
80887>>>>>
80887>>>>>
80887>>>>>    //***
80887>>>>>    //*** Function: BrowseConnect
80887>>>>>    //*** Purpose : Call the driver's browse connect function
80887>>>>>    //***
80887>>>>>
80887>>>>>    Function BrowseConnect String sInConnStr Returns String
80889>>>>>        Local String  sDriver
80889>>>>>        Local String  sOutConnStr
80889>>>>>        Local Integer iArg
80889>>>>>        Local Integer iRetval
80889>>>>>
80889>>>>>        Get psDriverID To sDriver
80890>>>>>        If (sDriver <> "") Begin
80892>>>>>            Move (Repeat(" ", 8192)) To sOutConnStr
80893>>>>>            Call_Driver 0 sDRiver Function CLI_BROWSECONNECT Callback 0 Passing sInConnStr sOutConnStr iArg Result iRetval
80898>>>>>        End
80898>>>>>>
80898>>>>>
80898>>>>>        Function_Return sOutConnStr
80899>>>>>    End_Function// BrowseConnect
80900>>>>>
80900>>>>>
80900>>>>>    Function BrowseConnectLocal String sInConnStr Returns String
80902>>>>>        Local String  sDriver
80902>>>>>        Local String  sOutConnStr
80902>>>>>        Local Integer iArg
80902>>>>>        Local Integer iRetval
80902>>>>>        
80902>>>>>        Move 1 to iArg // Browses only local
80903>>>>>
80903>>>>>        Get psDriverID to sDriver
80904>>>>>        If (sDriver <> "") Begin
80906>>>>>            Move (Repeat(" ", 8192)) to sOutConnStr
80907>>>>>            Call_Driver 0 sDRiver Function CLI_BROWSECONNECT Callback 0 Passing sInConnStr sOutConnStr iArg Result iRetval
80912>>>>>        End
80912>>>>>>
80912>>>>>
80912>>>>>        Function_Return sOutConnStr
80913>>>>>    End_Function// BrowseConnect
80914>>>>>
80914>>>>>
80914>>>>>    Function DriverIndex String sDriver Returns Integer
80916>>>>>    
80916>>>>>        Local String  sCurrentDriver
80916>>>>>        Local Integer iNumberOfDrivers iDriver iCount
80916>>>>>    
80916>>>>>        Move 0 to iDriver
80917>>>>>    
80917>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_NUMBER_DRIVERS to iNumberOfDrivers
80920>>>>>        For iCount from 1 to iNumberOfDrivers
80926>>>>>>
80926>>>>>    
80926>>>>>            Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_NAME of iCount to sCurrentDriver
80929>>>>>            If ( Uppercase(sCurrentDriver) = Uppercase(sDriver) ) Begin
80931>>>>>                Move iCount to iDriver
80932>>>>>            End
80932>>>>>>
80932>>>>>        Loop
80933>>>>>>
80933>>>>>    
80933>>>>>        Function_Return iDriver
80934>>>>>    
80934>>>>>    End_Function 
80935>>>>>
80935>>>>>    Function EnumerateServersNetworkOrLocal Integer iNetworkLocal  Returns Integer
80937>>>>>        
80937>>>>>        Local String  sServerList
80937>>>>>        Local Integer iNumServers
80937>>>>>        Local Integer iDriver
80937>>>>>        Local Integer iClientVersion
80937>>>>>        Local String  sDriver
80937>>>>>        
80937>>>>>        Get DriverIndex MSSQLDRV_ID to iDriver
80938>>>>>
80938>>>>>        If (iDriver) Begin
80940>>>>>                
80940>>>>>            Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_SQLSERVER_CLIENT_VERSION of iDriver to iClientVersion
80943>>>>>            
80943>>>>>            Case Begin
80943>>>>>    
80943>>>>>                Case (iClientVersion = SQLSERVER2016CLIENT)
80945>>>>>                    Move SQLSERVER2016DRVRSTR to sDriver
80946>>>>>                    Case Break
80947>>>>>    
80947>>>>>                Case (iClientVersion = SQLSERVER2014CLIENT)
80950>>>>>                    Move SQLSERVER2014DRVRSTR to sDriver
80951>>>>>                    Case Break
80952>>>>>            
80952>>>>>                Case (iClientVersion = SQLSERVER2012CLIENT)
80955>>>>>                    Move SQLSERVER2012DRVRSTR to sDriver
80956>>>>>                    Case Break
80957>>>>>    
80957>>>>>                Case (iClientVersion = SQLSERVER2008CLIENT)
80960>>>>>                    Move SQLSERVER2008DRVRSTR to sDriver
80961>>>>>                    Case Break
80962>>>>>    
80962>>>>>                Case (iClientVersion = SQLSERVER2005CLIENT)
80965>>>>>                    Move SQLSERVER2005DRVRSTR to sDriver
80966>>>>>                    Case Break
80967>>>>>            
80967>>>>>                Case (iClientVersion = SQLSERVER2000CLIENT)
80970>>>>>                    Move SQLSERVER2000DRVRSTR to sDriver
80971>>>>>                    Case Break
80972>>>>>            
80972>>>>>                Case Else
80972>>>>>                    Move SQLSERVER2000DRVRSTR to sDriver
80973>>>>>            
80973>>>>>            Case End
80973>>>>>    
80973>>>>>            Move ("DRIVER={" + sDriver + "};") to sDriver
80974>>>>>            If (iNetworkLocal = 0) Begin
80976>>>>>                Get BrowseConnect sDriver to sServerList
80977>>>>>            End
80977>>>>>>
80977>>>>>            Else Begin
80978>>>>>                Get BrowseConnectLocal sDriver to sServerList
80979>>>>>            End
80979>>>>>>
80979>>>>>            Get ExtractList sServerList Current_object to iNumServers
80980>>>>>        End
80980>>>>>>
80980>>>>>        
80980>>>>>        Function_Return iNumServers
80981>>>>>        
80981>>>>>    End_Function
80982>>>>>
80982>>>>>    //***
80982>>>>>    //*** Procedure: EnumerateServers
80982>>>>>    //*** Purpose  : Enumerate the available SQL Server database servers
80982>>>>>    //***            This function will return all SQL Server instances on the network. 
80982>>>>>    //***            This may take a long time. 
80982>>>>>    //***            To enumerate only local SQL Server instances use EnumerateServersLocal 
80982>>>>>    Function EnumerateServers Returns Integer
80984>>>>>
80984>>>>>        Local Integer iNumServers
80984>>>>>        Local Integer iNetworkLocal
80984>>>>>        
80984>>>>>        Move 0 to iNetworkLocal // 0 = enumerate network servers
80985>>>>>        
80985>>>>>        Get EnumerateServersNetworkOrLocal iNetworkLocal to iNumServers
80986>>>>>        
80986>>>>>        Function_Return iNumServers
80987>>>>>        
80987>>>>>    End_Function
80988>>>>>
80988>>>>>
80988>>>>>    //***
80988>>>>>    //*** Procedure: EnumerateServersLocal
80988>>>>>    //*** Purpose  : Enumerate the available SQL Server database servers
80988>>>>>    //***            This function will return only return SQL Server instance on the local machine
80988>>>>>    //***            To enumerate all SQL Server instances in a network use EnumerateServers
80988>>>>>    Function EnumerateServersLocal Returns Integer
80990>>>>>
80990>>>>>        Local Integer iNumServers
80990>>>>>        Local Integer iNetworkLocal
80990>>>>>        
80990>>>>>        Move 1 to iNetworkLocal // 1 = enumerate local servers
80991>>>>>        
80991>>>>>        Get EnumerateServersNetworkOrLocal iNetworkLocal to iNumServers
80992>>>>>        
80992>>>>>        Function_Return iNumServers
80993>>>>>        
80993>>>>>    End_Function
80994>>>>>
80994>>>>>    
80994>>>>>
80994>>>>>    //***
80994>>>>>    //*** Function: EnumerateDatabases
80994>>>>>    //*** Purpose : Enumerate database in a given server.
80994>>>>>    //***
80994>>>>>
80994>>>>>    Function EnumerateDatabases String sServer String sUser String sPassWord Returns Integer
80996>>>>>        Local Integer hoSQL
80996>>>>>        Local String  sConnect
80996>>>>>        Local String  sDatabase
80996>>>>>        Local Integer hdbc
80996>>>>>        Local Integer hstmt
80996>>>>>        Local Integer iFetchResult
80996>>>>>
80996>>>>>        If (Num_Arguments < 3) ;            Move "" To sPassWord
80999>>>>>        If (Num_Arguments < 2) ;            Move "" To sUser
81002>>>>>
81002>>>>>        If (sUser <> "") ;            Move ("SERVER=" + Trim(sServer) + ";UID=" + Trim(sUser) + ";PWD=" + Trim(sPassword) + ";") To sConnect
81005>>>>>        Else ;            Move ("SERVER=" + Trim(sServer) + ";Trusted_Connection=yes") To sConnect
81007>>>>>
81007>>>>>        Object oEnumDBSQLmanager Is A cSQLHandleManager
81009>>>>>            Move Current_Object To hoSQL
81010>>>>>        End_Object // oEnumDBSQLManager
81011>>>>>
81011>>>>>        If (hoSQL <> 0) Begin
81013>>>>>            Get SQLConnect Of hoSQL "MSSQLDRV" sConnect To hdbc
81014>>>>>            If (hdbc <> 0) Begin
81016>>>>>                Get SQLOpen Of hdbc To hstmt
81017>>>>>                If (hstmt <> 0) Begin
81019>>>>>                    //*** We could do a direct select on the sysdatabases table but we use
81019>>>>>                    //*** the stored procedure sp_database instead. SQL Server recommends this
81019>>>>>                    //*** approach in case meta data might change, the stored procedure will
81019>>>>>                    //*** stay the same.
81019>>>>>                    Send SQLSetProcedureName To hstmt "sp_databases"
81020>>>>>                    Send SQLCall To hstmt
81021>>>>>                    Repeat
81021>>>>>>
81021>>>>>                        Get SQLFetch Of hstmt To iFetchResult
81022>>>>>                        If (iFetchResult <> 0) Begin
81024>>>>>                            Get SQLColumnValue Of hstmt 1 To sDatabase
81025>>>>>                            Set Value Item (Item_Count(Current_Object)) To sDatabase
81026>>>>>                        End
81026>>>>>>
81026>>>>>                    Until (iFetchResult = 0)
81028>>>>>
81028>>>>>                    Send SQLClose To hstmt
81029>>>>>                End
81029>>>>>>
81029>>>>>                Send SQLDisconnect To hdbc
81030>>>>>            End
81030>>>>>>
81030>>>>>        End
81030>>>>>>
81030>>>>>        Send Destroy_Object To hoSQL
81031>>>>>
81031>>>>>        Function_return (Item_Count(Current_Object))
81032>>>>>    End_Function // EnumerateDatabases
81033>>>>>
81033>>>>>
81033>>>>>    Function SqlServerClientVersionName Integer iClientVersion  Returns String
81035>>>>>        
81035>>>>>        Local String  sSqlServerClientVersionName
81035>>>>>        
81035>>>>>            
81035>>>>>        Case Begin
81035>>>>>
81035>>>>>            Case (iClientVersion = SQLSERVER2016CLIENT)
81037>>>>>                Move SQLSERVER2016CLIENTNAME to sSqlServerClientVersionName
81038>>>>>                Case Break
81039>>>>>
81039>>>>>            Case (iClientVersion = SQLSERVER2014CLIENT)
81042>>>>>                Move SQLSERVER2014CLIENTNAME to sSqlServerClientVersionName
81043>>>>>                Case Break
81044>>>>>        
81044>>>>>            Case (iClientVersion = SQLSERVER2012CLIENT)
81047>>>>>                Move SQLSERVER2012CLIENTNAME to sSqlServerClientVersionName
81048>>>>>                Case Break
81049>>>>>
81049>>>>>            Case (iClientVersion = SQLSERVER2008CLIENT)
81052>>>>>                Move SQLSERVER2008CLIENTNAME to sSqlServerClientVersionName
81053>>>>>                Case Break
81054>>>>>
81054>>>>>            Case (iClientVersion = SQLSERVER2005CLIENT)
81057>>>>>                Move SQLSERVER2005CLIENTNAME to sSqlServerClientVersionName
81058>>>>>                Case Break
81059>>>>>        
81059>>>>>            Case (iClientVersion = SQLSERVER2000CLIENT)
81062>>>>>                Move SQLSERVER2000CLIENTNAME to sSqlServerClientVersionName
81063>>>>>                Case Break
81064>>>>>        
81064>>>>>            Case Else
81064>>>>>                Move SQLSERVERUNKNOWNCLIENTNAME to sSqlServerClientVersionName
81065>>>>>        
81065>>>>>        Case End
81065>>>>>    
81065>>>>>        
81065>>>>>        Function_Return sSqlServerClientVersionName
81066>>>>>        
81066>>>>>    End_Function
81067>>>>>
81067>>>>>
81067>>>>>End_Class // cMSSQLHandler
