81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_SET_MODE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Allows switching between set-oriented and record oriented fetch modes.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// If DF_FILE_SET_MODE is set to True, the driver will fetch a set of records
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// for each find. If DF_FILE_SET_MODE is False, the driver will fetch only one
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// record at a time. This attribute can also be specified in the .INT file during
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// migration through Flex2SQL. This settings is normally used alongside
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS to set the number of rows to return and DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// to turn on local caching.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Note: Turning off set-mode can have a detrimental impact on performance. Unless
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// there is a specific reason to do otherwise, this option should be left on.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Default value: True
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-15 by Oliver Nelson
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT OPTIMIZE {FOR_SET | ONE_ROW}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_SET_MODE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_SET_MODE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Mode for the FileNumber. True for set-mode, False for one-row mode.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Orderhea
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Set_Attribute DF_FILE_SET_MODE of Orderhea.File_Number to True
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_SET_MODE of Orderhea.File_Number to boolVar
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_SET_MODE                             For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+5)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_DATABASENAME
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Returns a string containing the name of the database where the
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// table referenced by the passed File Number resides. This is a READ ONLY
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// attribute. Note that because Oracle doesn't support the concept of multiple
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// databases on one server, this attribute is not valid for Oracle.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex, MySQLFlex, PGFlex
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-15 by Oliver Nelson
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_DATABASENAME of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Name of the Database
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Orderhea
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_DATABASENAME of Orderhea.File_Number to strVal
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_DATABASENAME                         For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+6)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Controls the maximum number of rows retrieved by a Find GT/LT
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// operation. The driver will automatically retrieve and cache this many rows
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// for future find GT/LT operations. Setting this property to a very high
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// value can be inefficient from a UI perspective but may be advisable for
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// local processing of rows (such as in a batch process).
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Default value: 10
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-15 by Oliver Nelson
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See DF_FILE_SET_MODE DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT MAX_ROWS_TO_QUERY {integer}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_DATABASENAME of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Attribute Value
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Orderhea
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Set_Attribute DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS of Orderhea.File_Number to 10
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS of Orderhea.File_Number to intVal
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS                             For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+7)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_TABLE_NAME
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Use this attribute to set or get the name of the SQL table
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// corresponding to the specified file number. In a restructure operation
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// this attribute may be used to permanently change the table that a filelist
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// entry is pointing to.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
