81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Activates or deactivates the local cache for set-oriented searches.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Through the DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE attribute, we can activate or deactivate the
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// local cache. When the cache is active in a set-oriented search, a fixed
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// number of records are pre-fetched and kept in the local cache. If a record
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// is not found in the local cache, a new set is fetched. The number of records
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// fetched is controlled via the DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS attribute. Set-mode vs. one-row
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// mode is controlled via the DF_FILE_SET_MODE attribute.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Note: Turning off the cache can have significant detrimental effects on performance.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Default value: True
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-15 by Oliver Nelson
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See         DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS DF_FILE_SET_MODE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Mode for FileNumber. True for active. False for inactive.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Orderhea
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Set_Attribute DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE of Orderhea.File_Number to True
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE of Orderhea.File_Number to boolVal
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE                           For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+9)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//Currently Unsupported Attribute
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_STORAGE_BASE                         For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+10)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_STATIC
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Activates or deactivates a special table mode where all rows
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// from the table are loaded into a local cache. When active, all searches are
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// done in memory and the actual table is not accessed.  The driver does not allow
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// editing of a table in static mode.  This is a very useful feature especially
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// when a table contains configuration or static information used in
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// calculations, (i.e., Tax Rate tables, etc.) By keeping this table locally
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// in memory, network round trips are saved resulting in significant
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// performance improvements. This attribute is also useful for batch
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// processes that make extensive table IO requests for reading static information.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Note: Because the entire table is loaded into memory, it is inadvisable to use
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// this on very large tables.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Default value: False
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-15 by Oliver Nelson
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_STATIC of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Static Mode for FileNumber. True for static. False for dynamic.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Orderhea
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Set_Attribute DF_FILE_STATIC of Orderhea.File_Number to True
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_STATIC of Orderhea.File_Number to boolVal
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_STATIC                               For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+11)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_SERVER_NAME
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Use this attribute to set or get the name of the database server
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// corresponding to the specified file number. In a restructure operation
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// this attribute may be used to permanently change the server that a filelist
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// entry is pointing to.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-15 by Oliver Nelson
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT SERVER_NAME {string}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_SERVER_NAME of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_SERVER_NAME of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Name of the database server.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Orderhea
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Set_Attribute DF_FILE_SERVER_NAME of Orderhea.File_Number to "(localdb)\v11.0"
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_SERVER_NAME of Orderhea.File_Number to strVal
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_SERVER_NAME                          For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+12)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
