81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_GET_SERVERNAME_FROM_LOGIN
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Use this attribute to specify whether the SERVER_NAME option will
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// be included in the INT file.  If set to True, the SERVER_NAME option will not
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// be included in the INT file, if set to false, the SERVER_NAME option will be
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// included in the INT file. This has two uses. The first is during a Structure_Start
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// i.e. table creation/modification. The other is when using the OUTPUT_INT_FILE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// command. Set this attribute before the OUTPUT_INT_FILE to indicate how the INT
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// file will be written. This name indicates a backwards logic so take note that
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// setting it to true will NOT include the SERVER_NAME in the INT file.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Default Value: False
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Deprecated
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-01 by Aaron Gulack
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See         DF_FILE_SUPPRESS_SERVERNAME_OUTPUT
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT              SERVER_NAME
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_GET_SERVERNAME_FROM_LOGIN of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_GET_SERVERNAME_FROM_LOGIN of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Boolean variable. True to not include, false to include in INT.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Set_Attribute DF_FILE_GET_SERVERNAME_FROM_LOGIN of Customer.File_Number to True
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     OUTPUT_INT_FILE for Customer.File_Number to "c:\temp\test.int"
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Close Customer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_GET_SERVERNAME_FROM_LOGIN            For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+29)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_SUPPRESS_SERVERNAME_OUTPUT
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Use this attribute to specify whether the SERVER_NAME option will be included
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// in the INT file.  If set to True, the server name will not be included in the INT file,
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// if set to false, the server name will be included in the INT file. This has two uses.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// The first is during a Structure_Start i.e. table creation/modification. The other is
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// when using the OUTPUT_INT_FILE command. Set this attribute before the OUTPUT_INT_FILE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// to indicate how the INT file will be written.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Default Value: False
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-01 by Aaron Gulack
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See         DF_FILE_SUPPRESS_DATABASENAME_OUTPUT DF_FILE_SUPPRESS_SCHEMANAME_OUTPUT
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT              SERVER_NAME
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_SUPPRESS_SERVERNAME_OUTPUT of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_SUPPRESS_SERVERNAME_OUTPUT of {FileNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Boolean variable. True to not include, false to include in INT.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///   Set_Attribute DF_FILE_SUPPRESS_SERVERNAME_OUTPUT of Customer.File_Number to True
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///   OUTPUT_INT_FILE for Customer.File_Number to "c:\temp\test.int"
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Close Customer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_SUPPRESS_SERVERNAME_OUTPUT                       For DF_FILE_GET_SERVERNAME_FROM_LOGIN
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
