81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FIELD_NULL
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Use this attribute to get or set whether a column in a table will
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// allow null values. When set to true, the column accepts null values. Setting
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// this attribute to false will keep it from accepting null values. Although,
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// getting the value of this attribute can be done at anytime, setting it must
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// be done in a Structure_Start or during table creation.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-09 by Aaron Gulack
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FIELD_NULL of {FileNumber} {FieldNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FIELD_NULL of {FileNumber} {FieldNumber} to {variable}
