81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FieldNumber                 Number of the Field
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable                    Boolean variable
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Handle hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Integer iColumn
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Boolean bAllowNull
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Move Customer.File_Number to hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Move 3 to iColumn
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Structure_Start hFile "ORA_DRV"
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///    Set_Attribute DF_FIELD_NULL of hFile iColumn to True
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Structure_End hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FIELD_NULL of hFile iColumn to bAllowNull
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FIELD_NULL                                For (DF_FIELD_NATIVE_LENGTH+10)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FIELD_NATIVE_TYPE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Use this attribute to get or set the Native type for a specific
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// field in a table.  The native type refers to the data type of the field on the
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// SQL backend. Setting this attribute can only be done during table creation or
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// inside of a Structure_Start. When setting this attribute, it is good practice
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// to use the constants mentioned below instead of the integers. For a list of
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// these constants, refer to the sections: "Oracle Data Types", "MySQL Data Types",
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// "PostgreSQL Data Types", and "SQL Server Data Types" included in this document.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Note that when getting the value for this attribute, an integer will be returned
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// so these lists of constants can again prove useful.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-09 by Aaron Gulack
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT      FIELD_TYPE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FIELD_NATIVE_TYPE of {FileNumber} {FieldNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FIELD_NATIVE_TYPE of {FileNumber} {FieldNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber          Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FieldNumber         Number of the field
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable                    variable for the native data type
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// open Customer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Integer iColumn iType
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Handle hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Move Customer.File_Number to hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Structure_Start hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Set_Attribute DF_FIELD_NATIVE_TYPE of hFile iColumn to "eSQLServer_DATE"
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Get_Attribute DF_FIELD_NATIVE_TYPE of hFile iColumn to iType
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Structure_End hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FIELD_NATIVE_TYPE                         For (DF_FIELD_NATIVE_LENGTH+12)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Currently Unsupported Attribute (readOnly used by DataFlex 18.0 Studio)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FIELD_NATIVE_TYPE_NAME                    For 711
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Currently Unsupported Attribute
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FIELD_NATIVE_OFFSET                       For (DF_FIELD_NATIVE_LENGTH+14)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FIELD_AUTO_INCREMENT
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description Auto incrementing is a technique used in Dataflex usually for
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// fields that are set as the unique identifier. Instead of generating a value
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// or manually inserting data into the column, when a field auto increments,
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// the value of the field increases by one (usually) with each record.  This
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// field is used to get or set whether the field uses this technique or not.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// The attribute, however, can only be set inside of a Structure_Start or during
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// table creation. Getting the attribute's value can be done at anytime. The
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// value is stored as a boolean, either true or false.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-12 by Aaron Gulack
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT      FIELD_AUTOINCREMENT_TYPE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FIELD_AUTO_INCREMENT of {FileNumber} {FieldNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FIELD_AUTO_INCREMENT of {FileNumber} {FieldNumber} to {variable}
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber          Number of the file
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  FieldNumber         Number of the field
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable                    Boolean variable indicating if the field auto increments.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// open Customer
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Integer iColumn
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Boolean bIncrement
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Handle hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Move Customer.File_Number to hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// Structure_Start hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Set_Attribute DF_FIELD_AUTO_INCREMENT of hFile iColumn to True
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Get_Attribute DF_FIELD_AUTO_INCREMENT of hFile iColumn to bIncrement
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///     Structure_End hFile
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FIELD_AUTO_INCREMENT                      For (DF_FIELD_NATIVE_LENGTH+16)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>//Currently Unsupported Attribute
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FIELD_GENERATE_ALWAYS                     For (DF_FIELD_NATIVE_LENGTH+18)
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Currently Unsupported Attribute
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>Define DF_FIELD_SEND_LONG_DATA                      For 702
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>
