81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_INDEX_UNIQUE
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description An index on a column that is unique is considered so if it
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// does not have two equal values in that column in two different rows. This
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// attribute is used to find out whether or not the specified index is unique.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// If it is, this attribute will return "U" indicating that it is indeed unique.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// This is important to note because when getting the value of this attribute,
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// a string variable must be used. Since this is a ReadOnly attribute, setting
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// an idex to unique cannot be done with this attribute.
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
81359>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
