82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        SET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to set the number of milliseconds
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// an SQL statement waits for a database lock to be released before timing
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// out. Locks are used with transactions to maintain atomicity. If a lock is
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// not released before the timeout, then the statement will fail and an error
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// will be raised. By default, the timeout is set to -1, indicating that
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// statements will wait indefinitely before timing out.
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-07 by Aaron Gulack
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See                 GET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SET_SQL_LOCAL_TIMEOUT of {server} to {variable}
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param server                       Name of the server
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Number of milliseconds to wait until timeout
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// SET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT of "localhost" to 6000
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        GET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description This command returns the number of milliseconds an SQL
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// statement will wait for a database lock to be released. If the lock
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// is not released before the timeout, then the statement will fail and
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// an error will be raised. Note that the default value is -1, indicating
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// that the statement will wait indefinitely.
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-07 by Aaron Gulack
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @See                 SET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Syntax GET_SQL_LOCAL_TIMEOUT of {server} to {variable}
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param server                       Name of the server
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Variable to hold the number of milliseconds
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Example
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// GET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT of "localhost" to iTimeout
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>
82390>>>>>>>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
