82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Name        SET_AUTHENTICATION_MODE
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to control what mode the user logs
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// in as. When DEFAULT is passed, the user will be logged in with the
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// default privileges given to it. When SYSDBA is passed, the user will
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// be logged in with the roles assigned to the sysdba user, most likely
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// full control over the database.
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>///
82455>>>>>>>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
