84073>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure SQLSetNextArgument String sArgument
84075>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iArgnum
84075>>>>>>>>>>>
84075>>>>>>>>>>>        Get piLastArgument to iArgnum
84076>>>>>>>>>>>        Increment iArgnum
84077>>>>>>>>>>>        Send SQLSetArgument iArgnum sArgument
84078>>>>>>>>>>>        Set piLastArgument to iArgnum
84079>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure // SQLSetNextArgument
84080>>>>>>>>>>>    
84080>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure SQLSetArgument Integer iArgnum String sArgument
84082>>>>>>>>>>>        Variant[] vParams
84083>>>>>>>>>>>        
84083>>>>>>>>>>>        Get pvParams to vParams
84084>>>>>>>>>>>        Move sArgument to vParams[iArgnum-1]
84085>>>>>>>>>>>        Set pvParams to vParams
84086>>>>>>>>>>>    
84086>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure // SQLSetArgument
84087>>>>>>>>>>>    
84087>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure SQLCall
84089>>>>>>>>>>>        Variant[] vParams
84090>>>>>>>>>>>        Variant[] vParamOpts
84091>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer i
84091>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iMax
84091>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iParamsIn 
84091>>>>>>>>>>>        String sParameter
84091>>>>>>>>>>>        Boolean bIsProcedure
84091>>>>>>>>>>>        
84091>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CURRENT_CURSOR_STMT to (piCursorNum(Self))
84105>>>>>>>>>>>>
84105>>>>>>>>>>>        
84105>>>>>>>>>>>        Get pvParams to vParams
84106>>>>>>>>>>>        
84106>>>>>>>>>>>        // First, we need to figure out if this is a procedure or a function. Then if
84106>>>>>>>>>>>        // it's a procedure, "analyze" it to figure out which parameters are IN, 
84106>>>>>>>>>>>        // OUT, or IN_OUT.  Then we adjust how we call SQL_SET_PROCEDURE_PARAMETER
84106>>>>>>>>>>>        // so that after the call you can retrieve the value.
84106>>>>>>>>>>>        
84106>>>>>>>>>>>        Get IsProcedure (psProcName(Self)) to bIsProcedure
84107>>>>>>>>>>>        
84107>>>>>>>>>>>        If (bIsProcedure) Begin
84109>>>>>>>>>>>            Get ProcParams (psProcName(Self)) to vParamOpts
84110>>>>>>>>>>>            
84110>>>>>>>>>>>            Move (sizeOfArray(vParamOpts)) to iMax
84111>>>>>>>>>>>            Move (SizeOfArray(vParams)) to iParamsIn
84112>>>>>>>>>>>            Set piParameterCount to iMax
84113>>>>>>>>>>>            
84113>>>>>>>>>>>            SQL_SET_PROCEDURE_NAME (psProcName(Self)) NUMPAR iMax 
84133>>>>>>>>>>>            For i from 1 to iMax
84139>>>>>>>>>>>>
84139>>>>>>>>>>>                If ( (i-1) >= iParamsIn) Move "" to sParameter
84142>>>>>>>>>>>                Else Move vParams[i-1] to sParameter
84144>>>>>>>>>>>                
84144>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Begin
84144>>>>>>>>>>>                    Case (vParamOpts[i-1] = "IN")
84146>>>>>>>>>>>                        SQL_SET_PROCEDURE_PARAMETER i to sParameter IN
84187>>>>>>>>>>>>
84187>>>>>>>>>>>                        Case Break
84188>>>>>>>>>>>                    Case (vParamOpts[i-1] = "OUT")
84191>>>>>>>>>>>                        SQL_SET_PROCEDURE_PARAMETER i to sParameter OUT
84232>>>>>>>>>>>>
84232>>>>>>>>>>>                        Case Break
84233>>>>>>>>>>>                    Case (vParamOpts[i-1] = "IN/OUT" or vParamOpts[i-1] = "INOUT")
84236>>>>>>>>>>>                        SQL_SET_PROCEDURE_PARAMETER i to sParameter IN_OUT
84277>>>>>>>>>>>>
84277>>>>>>>>>>>                        Case Break     
84278>>>>>>>>>>>                Case End
84278>>>>>>>>>>>            Loop
84279>>>>>>>>>>>>
84279>>>>>>>>>>>            
84279>>>>>>>>>>>            SQL_PROCEDURE_EXECUTE
84294>>>>>>>>>>>        End
84294>>>>>>>>>>>>
84294>>>>>>>>>>>        Else Begin
84295>>>>>>>>>>>            SQL_SET_FUNCTION_NAME (psProcName(Self)) NUMPAR (SizeOfArray(vParams))
84319>>>>>>>>>>>            For i from 1 to (SizeOfArray(vParams))
84325>>>>>>>>>>>>
84325>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_SET_FUNCTION_PARAMETER i to vParams[i-1]
84397>>>>>>>>>>>>
84397>>>>>>>>>>>            Loop
84398>>>>>>>>>>>>
84398>>>>>>>>>>>            
84398>>>>>>>>>>>            SQL_FUNCTION_EXECUTE
84399>>>>>>>>>>>        End
84399>>>>>>>>>>>>
84399>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
84400>>>>>>>>>>>
84400>>>>>>>>>>>    Function SQLGetNextArgument Returns String
84402>>>>>>>>>>>        Local Integer iArgnum
