94872>>>>>>>>>>>
94872>>>>>>>>>>>// Help System Package
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//
94872>>>>>>>>>>>// Public Properties that should be set:
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property String  Help_Filename   (Help_File_Default(self))
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_General 0
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Index   0
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Keys    0
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Files   0
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Errors  0
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//
94872>>>>>>>>>>>// Public messsages which are sent to this object:
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Context_KeyWord_Help integer Obj
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Context_ID_Help      integer Obj
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Context_Help         integer Obj
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Help_for_help        integer Obj
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_help_index           integer Obj
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Keys_Help            integer Obj
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_File_Help            integer Obj
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Error_Help           integer Obj
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Help_on_Topic        integer Obj
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//
94872>>>>>>>>>>>// Protected Messages:
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//        These messages invoke the Window's help system and are not
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//        directly sent by outside objects. They are sent by public
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//        "view_xxx" messages and might be used if you are creating
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//        a sub-class of an object-class.
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    Procedure Exec_System_Context_Help  integer Context_id
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    Procedure Exec_System_Help          string  Keyword
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    Procedure Exec_Context_Help         string  Context
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    Functions for converting DF help IDs to windows Help Ids
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//        Any of these can return either a string or an integer.
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    Function System_Help_Context_id Integer ID Returns String
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//           Convert a DF help context id into a windows id. By default,
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//           just return the same value (a one to one match). This is called
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//           by View_Context_id_help and View_Context_Help
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    Function System_Help_File_Id Integer File# Integer Field# Returns String
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//           Convert file and field into a help id. By default it returns the
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//           file#. Called by View_File_Help.
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//    Function System_Help_Error_id Integer Id Returns String
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//           Convert an error message into an ID. Right now it returns the
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//           the general error context id property, Help_id_errors. This
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//           will invoke general error help. If you want error support at the
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//           error# level you will have to determine the program to help
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//           interface yourself. Errors have a very large range and it is
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//           therefore hard to come up with an automatic numbering scheme.
94872>>>>>>>>>>>//           Called by View_Error_Help.
94872>>>>>>>>>>>
94872>>>>>>>>>>>
94872>>>>>>>>>>>Use Windows.pkg
94872>>>>>>>>>>>Use WinHlp.pkg // low level help call to windows API provides global message gDoWinHelp
94872>>>>>>>>>>>Use HelpSystemConstants.pkg // constants used by help system
94872>>>>>>>>>>>
94872>>>>>>>>>>>Register_Function phoWorkspace Returns Handle
94872>>>>>>>>>>>Register_function peHelpType  returns integer
94872>>>>>>>>>>>
94872>>>>>>>>>>>class HelpSystem is an cObject
94873>>>>>>>>>>>
94873>>>>>>>>>>>    register_function Help_File_Default returns string
94873>>>>>>>>>>>
94873>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure Construct_Object
94875>>>>>>>>>>>       Forward send Construct_Object
94877>>>>>>>>>>>
94877>>>>>>>>>>>       // Help file name only. If set, this overrides all other settings.
94877>>>>>>>>>>>       Property String psHelpFile
94878>>>>>>>>>>>
94878>>>>>>>>>>>       // Help_FileName
94878>>>>>>>>>>>       //   full path name of Help file. The default value grabs its value
94878>>>>>>>>>>>       //   from .ini or environment settings. See functiob Help_file_Default
94878>>>>>>>>>>>       //
94878>>>>>>>>>>>       Property String  Private.Help_Filename (Help_File_Default(self))
94879>>>>>>>>>>>
94879>>>>>>>>>>>       // The following properties are the default values for the help files
94879>>>>>>>>>>>       // IDs for the various subjects. Setting these requires an agreement
94879>>>>>>>>>>>       // between the DF help system and the help file.
94879>>>>>>>>>>>       //
94879>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_General  0
94880>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Index    0
94881>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Keys     0
94882>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Files    0
94883>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Errors   0
94884>>>>>>>>>>>
94884>>>>>>>>>>>       // this is now the default help object
94884>>>>>>>>>>>       Move self to Help_Object_id
94885>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
94886>>>>>>>>>>>
94886>>>>>>>>>>>   // New rules for VDF8:
94886>>>>>>>>>>>   // 1. If psHelpFile exists, find the file in the file path and use it
94886>>>>>>>>>>>   // 2. If application object exists and help type is windows, use psHelpFile from there, find in file path and use it.
94886>>>>>>>>>>>   // 3. If no help file exists, use thge old private help name (which gets the full name from the registry -only if no app object)
94886>>>>>>>>>>>   //    Last method is deprecated and only used for old applications
94886>>>>>>>>>>>   //
94886>>>>>>>>>>>   Function Help_filename returns string
94888>>>>>>>>>>>        string sHelpName
94888>>>>>>>>>>>        // If ghoWorkSpace Get Help_FileName of ghoWorkSpace to sHelpName // removed for VDF8
94888>>>>>>>>>>>
94888>>>>>>>>>>>        // If an Application object is used, take the name from there.
94888>>>>>>>>>>>        Get psHelpFile to sHelpName
94889>>>>>>>>>>>        If (sHelpName="" AND ghoApplication AND peHelpType(ghoApplication)=htWinHelp) Begin
94891>>>>>>>>>>>            Get psHelpFile of ghoApplication To sHelpName
94892>>>>>>>>>>>            //Move (psHelpPath(phoWorkspace(ghoApplication)) -"\" -sHelpName) To sHelpName
94892>>>>>>>>>>>        End
94892>>>>>>>>>>>>
94892>>>>>>>>>>>        If (sHelpName<>"") begin
94894>>>>>>>>>>>            Get_File_Path sHelpName To sHelpName
94895>>>>>>>>>>>            Function_Return sHelpName
94896>>>>>>>>>>>        end
94896>>>>>>>>>>>>
94896>>>>>>>>>>>        // if not set anywhere (and ideally it is) we use this.
94896>>>>>>>>>>>        Get Private.Help_FileName to sHelpName
94897>>>>>>>>>>>        Function_Return sHelpName
94898>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
94899>>>>>>>>>>>
94899>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure Set Help_FileName string sName
94901>>>>>>>>>>>        Set Private.Help_FileName to sName
94902>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
94903>>>>>>>>>>>
94903>>>>>>>>>>>
94903>>>>>>>>>>>
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    // Consider this message PRIVATE in that it should only be changed
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    // by a sub-class and not an object. It is called in construct_object
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    // before it knows about object augmentations!!!!
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    //  Sets the Help_file_name by looking at the .INI file for:
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    //        HELP_DIR    - help directory (will check environment variable
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    //                      windir if not found - avoid this usage). If not
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    //                      blank append "\" as required.
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    //        HELP_FILE   - help file name. If blank uses the default help
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    //                      file name
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94903>>>>>>>>>>>    Function Help_File_Default Returns String
94905>>>>>>>>>>>       String HelpFileDir HelpFileName sSubKey
94905>>>>>>>>>>>       // if using the application object we expect the help name to be
94905>>>>>>>>>>>       // defined in the application object or directly in the help object. No Exceptions
94905>>>>>>>>>>>       If (ghoApplication) function_return ""
94908>>>>>>>>>>>
94908>>>>>>>>>>>       // else if no application (and hence no WS) use an old deprecated method of checking
94908>>>>>>>>>>>       // for the module name in local_machine.
94908>>>>>>>>>>>       Get Module_name of Desktop to sSubKey
94909>>>>>>>>>>>       Get_Profile_String sSubKey HELP_DIR to HelpFileDir
94912>>>>>>>>>>>       Get_Profile_String sSubKey HELP_FILE to HelpFileName
94915>>>>>>>>>>>       // if dir exists, sure it has a "\" at the end. If no directory the
94915>>>>>>>>>>>       // dir must be blank so current directory is searched
94915>>>>>>>>>>>       If ( (HelpFileDir<>'') AND (Right(HelpFileDir,1)<>"\") ) ;          Move (HelpFileDir - '\') to HelpFileDir
94918>>>>>>>>>>>       If HelpFileName eq '' Move DEFAULT_HELP_FILENAME to HelpFileName
94921>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return (HelpFileDir - HelpFileName)
94922>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
94923>>>>>>>>>>>
94923>>>>>>>>>>>    // The System_Help_xxxx messages convert a DF help integer ID into
94923>>>>>>>>>>>    // a context value that can be used by the windows help system. If
94923>>>>>>>>>>>    // you return a number or a string. Numbers will get used for context ID
94923>>>>>>>>>>>    // help, non-numbers get used for keyword context help
94923>>>>>>>>>>>
94923>>>>>>>>>>>    // By default return ID passed. This creates a direct mapping between
94923>>>>>>>>>>>    // context IDs in your object and the context IDs in windows help.
94923>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94923>>>>>>>>>>>    Function System_Help_Context_id Integer ID Returns String
94925>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return ID
94926>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function // System_Help_Context_id
94927>>>>>>>>>>>
94927>>>>>>>>>>>    // Returns the file# which assumes that we have a direct mapping between
94927>>>>>>>>>>>    // the file number and a window's help context_id. We are ignoring field#
94927>>>>>>>>>>>    // in this case (although your augmentation would not have to). If the
94927>>>>>>>>>>>    // file# is 0, return a the HELP_ID context id.
94927>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94927>>>>>>>>>>>    Function System_Help_File_Id Integer File# Integer Field# Returns String
94929>>>>>>>>>>>       String rVal
94929>>>>>>>>>>>       if File# eq 0 Move (Help_id_files(self)) to rVal
94932>>>>>>>>>>>       Else Move File# to rVal
94934>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return Rval
94935>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function // System_Help_File_id
94936>>>>>>>>>>>
94936>>>>>>>>>>>    // Convert an error id into a help context id. Return the general
94936>>>>>>>>>>>    // Help id property value. We do this because error number have
94936>>>>>>>>>>>    // a rather large range (1-9000) and just using the number would consume
94936>>>>>>>>>>>    // too much of the context id space.
94936>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94936>>>>>>>>>>>    Function System_Help_Error_id Integer Id Returns String
94938>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return (Help_Id_Errors(self))
94939>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function // System_Help_Error_id
94940>>>>>>>>>>>
94940>>>>>>>>>>>    // Use this if you want your help context to be keyword based
94940>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94940>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure View_Context_KeyWord_Help integer Obj
94942>>>>>>>>>>>       String Context
94942>>>>>>>>>>>       If Obj gt 0 ;          Get Help_Context of obj HELP_CONTEXT_KEYWORD to Context
94945>>>>>>>>>>>       Send Exec_System_Help Context
94946>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
94947>>>>>>>>>>>
94947>>>>>>>>>>>    // Use this if you want your help context to be ID based
94947>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94947>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure View_Context_ID_Help integer Obj
94949>>>>>>>>>>>       Integer Context_ID
94949>>>>>>>>>>>       String Context
94949>>>>>>>>>>>       If Obj gt 0 ;          Get Help_Context of Obj HELP_CONTEXT_ID to Context_ID
94952>>>>>>>>>>>       Get System_Help_Context_id Context_Id to Context
94953>>>>>>>>>>>       Send Exec_Context_Help Context
94954>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
94955>>>>>>>>>>>
94955>>>>>>>>>>>    // Use this is you want the object requesting help to support either
94955>>>>>>>>>>>    // keyword or context ID help (it will use whatever it finds first).
94955>>>>>>>>>>>    //
94955>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure View_Context_Help integer Obj
94957>>>>>>>>>>>       String Context
94957>>>>>>>>>>>       If Obj gt 0 ;          Get Help_Context of obj HELP_CONTEXT_ID_OR_KEY to Context
94960>>>>>>>>>>>       if (left(context,1)) in '0123456789' ;          Get System_Help_Context_id Context to Context
94963>>>>>>>>>>>       Send Exec_Context_Help Context
94964>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
94965>>>>>>>>>>>
94965>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure View_Help_for_Help Integer obj
94967>>>>>>>>>>>        Send Exec_System_Help HELP_FOR_HELP_STRING
94968>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
94969>>>>>>>>>>>
94969>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure View_Help_Index integer obj
94971>>>>>>>>>>>       Send Exec_Context_Help (Help_id_index(self))
94972>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure // View_help_index
94973>>>>>>>>>>>
94973>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure View_Keys_Help Integer Obj
94975>>>>>>>>>>>        Send Exec_Context_Help (Help_id_keys(self))
